{"overview":"This A-minor fugue unfolds across 87 bars with a chromatically descending subject presented in successive voice entries before embarking on a carefully mapped modulatory journey through the relative and closely related keys (E minor, C major, F-sharp minor, D minor) via smooth diatonic pivot-chord modulations. Its most distinctive feature is the climactic stretto section, where the chromatic subject is compressed into tight imitative overlaps across five voices before resolving into a dense five-voice coda that seals the piece with a final authentic cadence.","cross_piece_tags":["fugue","counterpoint","chromatic_mediant","circle_of_fifths","modal_mixture","tragic","dramatic","melancholic"]}
